review_blob: Nice, light tasting beer from Belgium.  Drink cold.  Nice dry finish.
Barely passable.  This is a beer best drunk from a pitcher on a hot summer day.  Empty Canadian taste with a pretty colour.

There is nothing special about this beer.  It tastes like so many other mass-produced Canadian light lagers.  Bland, no distinctiveness, pop-like.
One compliment-the brewery is in a fabulous building and offers a good tour.
Very dark and malty.  Lingering bitterness.  Not quite the head I expected but I may have served it too cold.
A full-bodied pilsner with dry after-taste.
This is a bitter lager best drunk very cold in a hot setting.  The prefered beer in most of the caribbean for precisely that reason.  Goes well with fish and chicken or on its own.
Nice appearance.  Aroma is tart but not too bitter.  Very rich flavour with a great finish.  Best to drink it fairly cold.
Like watered-down real beer.  This is for beer drinkers who dont want the taste of real beer.  Like pop.  There is no maltiness or hoppiness at all.
Excellent lager. Skunky aroma and taste.  Full-bodied and refreshing.  Should be drunk ice cold.
Very light but watery and loses its flavour after a couple of pints.  Good if yourintention is to just have one or two.
MY favourite beer!!  Excellent full-bodied taste followed by a mellow chocolate after-taste.  Exquisite!
